* PRE REQUIREMENT (Linux)
- Install Weka & Add it`s jar location to your classpath

* COMPILE
- javac KCrossValidation.java

* RUN
- java -cp .:/usr/share/java/weka-3.6.10.jar KCrossValidation <filename> <validation_method>

<filename> -> iris.arff (or whatever .arff you have)
<validation_method> -> 
    - 1 : 10 fold cross validation
    - 2 : full training
    - 3 : testing (filename must be different from training)

nb : you have to make model from training (do validation_method 1 or 2), otherwise you can't test it (validation_method 3) 
